The paper deals with cryptographic protocols and their security in the presence of bounded storage adversaries. This falls under the category of "Cryptography and Security" (cs.CR). The paper also involves the use of information theory to analyze the protocols, which suggests a possible fit under "Information Theory" (cs.IT). The protocols also involve the use of computational complexity, which could place the paper under "Computational Complexity" (cs.CC). The paper also involves the use of data structures and algorithms to implement the protocols, which could place it under "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS). Finally, the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques to analyze the protocols, which could place it under "Machine Learning" (cs.LG).
